product.longDescription: For fresh use and storage. Makes nice cabbage even under fertility or weather stress. Firms up in as few as 75 days for fresh use, continuing to enlarge to 4-8 lb. for mid-fall harvest. The solid heads have delicious, crisp leaves, and are capable of long-term storage into spring. Flavor is superior to the typical cabbages available at the supermarket. Developed by cabbage breeder Don Reed, Cortland, NY. Avg. 113,300 seeds/lb. Packet: 100 seeds.
